There was one other sighting in Albuquerque on or around September 21st 2013
divs: Sighting DetailsWhile out walking our dogs, my wife first noticed several transparent clouds forming a ray like pattern parallel to one another about 25 degrees in the eastern sky. In the middle was what we thought to be Venus, but realized Venus was setting in the west. The object was bright, round, extremely distant, and stationary. The event lasted about 10 minutes. Unfortunately, we did not observed its disappearance.
Summary: Observed a star like object at dusk in eastern sky
